FBIS4-12175 "drnes066_r_94007" FBIS-NES-94-066 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 India Israel's Beilin Sees Potential for Cooperation Israel's Beilin Sees Potential for Cooperation TA0504064894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT Apr 94 TA0504064894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] After concluding his visit to New Delhi, Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin said that there is no reason for Israel not to sell arms to India. Beilin stressed, however, that he has no knowledge of any joint military plans between the two countries. Beilin asserted that the potential for cooperation between India and Israel is unlimited. The deputy foreign minister expressed the hope that India will become more involved in the peace process.
